<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 5:49PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Blowing snow reducing visibility in the Three Forks area...
Southwest winds are gusting in excess of 40 mph at times early
this evening in the Three Forks area, which is causing loose snow
to blow and drift in that area. Visibilities of five miles or
less are common in that immediate area, but periods of visibility
below two miles are possible. These conditions will likely persist
at least through this evening, making travel difficult, especially
over the portion of Interstate 90 in northwest Gallatin County.
Be aware that drifting snow will likely obscure potential icy
areas on the roadway. Drive with caution, and be ready for
changing road and visibility conditions.</description>
